Fiks i #559 for #639 er å slette en fil.

Det skjer om den er tom.

Programmatisk fiks:
Alternativ 1: curl -o fil http:vim/fil || rm fil
Alternativ 2: if(python) pyeval(fil) catch -> rm fil

Utgreing om eval og pyeval:
http://stackoverflow.com/a/19108243/200987

"Even though Vim's origin dates back a lot it happens that its internal string() eval() representation is that close to JSON that its likely to work unless you need special characters.
"

getfsize({fname}) size in bytes
filereadable( { file} )

File exists:
if !empty(glob("filename"))


Try catch
Use :try ... :catch: 
    function TrimTab() 
        try 
            %s/^tab//g 
        catch /^Vim(substitute):E486:/ 
            echo v:exception 
        endtry 
    endfunction 

Using pyeval
http://stackoverflow.com/a/13220941/200987

If you don’t you have recent vim you can emulate pyeval in this case:

function Pyeval(expr)
    python import json
    python vim.command('return '+json.dumps(eval(vim.eval('a:expr'))))
endfunction

You can test what Python version is available with: 
        if has('python')
          echo 'there is Python 2.x'
        elseif has('python3')
          echo 'there is Python 3.x'
        endif

